      • setDebugProcessingVertexGraphState

        public CompletableReactor setDebugProcessingVertexGraphState(boolean debugProcessingVertexGraphState)
        For debug purpose to add internal runtime vertex graph representation into result. This helps to find blocked vertices that does not completed correctly.

        If this flag is enabled then internal processing graph state will be attached to Execution result. This allows easy access to execution state during debug. One of drawbacks of this future is that GC will be prevented form removing internal state objects until all reference to execution result dies.

        Parameters:
        debugProcessingVertexGraphState - By default this flag is disabled.
